  "response": "The term \"Ankan Bivakar\" is not widely recognized in the context of fine arts education, and thus, it might not be considered a standard or universally accepted professional diploma in fine arts. The qualifications that are recognized as professional diplomas vary widely by country, institution, and field of specialization within the arts.\n\nIf \"Ankan Bivakar\" refers to a specific program or course offered by a particular institution, it would be necessary to look at the details of that program, including its curriculum, accreditation status, and recognition in the art community or industry, to determine its standing as a professional diploma.\n\nFor a qualification to be considered a professional diploma, it typically needs to be issued by a recognized educational institution and meet certain academic and professional standards. If you are considering enrolling in this or any similar program, it would be a good idea to research the institution offering it and seek reviews or feedback from alumni to better understand its value and recognition in the field of fine arts.",
